  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package contains a subtle W-EP-03 weakness: the primary experimental dataset carries a dataVintage predating the model's most recent revision; the assessment narrative argues the revision was not material to dataset relevance without formal re-validation.",
